               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Taʾammǝra ʾIyasus “Miracles of Jesus”: ca. 33 miracles (fols. 1ra-76vb),
                     incomplete.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- A few miracles are numbered: 13: <locus target="#6rb">6rb</locus>, 15:
                        9ra, 24: <locus target="#17va">17va</locus>, 25: <locus target="#21vb">21vb</locus>, 34: <locus target="#31vb">31vb</locus>, 37: 32rb, 7:
                           <locus target="#34va">34va</locus>, 36: <locus target="#47vb">47vb</locus>, 26: <locus target="#52rb">52rb</locus>, 30: <locus target="#63va">63va</locus>, 31: <locus target="#67ra">67ra</locus>, 32:
                           <locus target="#74vb">74vb</locus>, 33: <locus target="#76rb">76rb</locus>.</note>
                     <note>- Some of the miracles are introduced with the word taʾammǝr
                        “miracle”.</note>
                     <note>- The correct order of the fols. is as follows: 72, 33-38, 73, 1, 70, 71,
                        59, 2-9, 11-14, 27-30, 41, 39, 40, 42, 57, 58, 49, 51, 19, 16-18, 21, 24,
                        25, 20, 61, 52, 53, 15, 26, 54, 55, 62-69, 74-76, 44-48, 32.</note>
                     <note>The correct position of <locus target="#22">22</locus>, 23, 31, 43, 50,
                        56, 59, 60 has not been established.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="Codex">
                     <supportDesc>
                        <support>
                           <material key="parchment"/>
                        </support>
                        <extent>Made of <measure unit="leaf">76.0</measure> folios, in <measure unit="quire"/> quires . <dimensions type="outer">
                              <height unit="mm">255</height>
                              <width unit="mm">200</width>
                              <depth unit="mm">40</depth>
                           </dimensions>
                        </extent>
                        <foliation/>
                        <collation>
                           
                              The quire structure cannot be established due to the
                                 condition of the codex.
                           
                        </collation>
                        <condition key="deficient">Both boards and the original sewing are missing.
                           
 The Ms. is affected by water and possibly by fire (s. edges of
                              <locus from="32" to="38">32-38</locus>, 44-48). 
 Many fols. are
                           missing; the remaining fols. are misplaced. 
 Text in fols. 1-3,
                           70-73 is abraded. 
 Ink is washed out or faded in some fols.
                           Holes are amended on <locus target="#12">12</locus>, 13, 30.</condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout columns="2" writtenLines="20">
                           <dimensions unit="mm">
                              <height>170</height>
                              <width>147</width>
                              <dim type="intercolumn">18</dim>
                           </dimensions>
                           <dimensions type="margin">
                              <dim type="top">25</dim>
                              <dim type="bottom">55</dim>
                              <dim type="right">28</dim>
                              <dim type="left">15</dim>
                              <dim type="intercolumn">18</dim>
                           </dimensions>
                           <note>All data for <locus target="#4r">4r</locus>.</note>
                           <ab type="ruling"/>
                           <ab type="pricking">Pricking and ruling are visible. </ab>
                           <ab type="ruling" subtype="pattern"> Ruling pattern:
                              1A-1A-1A1A/0-0/0-0/C. </ab>
                           <ab type="pricking"> Primary pricks are visible. </ab>
                           <ab type="pricking"> Ruling pricks are visible (of slit-type). </ab>
                           <ab type="ruling"> The upper line is written above the ruling. </ab>
                           <ab type="ruling"> The bottom line is written above the ruling.</ab>
                        </layout>
                        <layout/>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Hand a: mediocre; hand b: mediocre</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (vivid red)</seg>
                        <date>Second half of the 19th cent. (?)</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; incipit of the miracles; elements of
                           the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">Hand a: <locus from="1r" to="10v">1r-10v</locus>, 15r-26v, 33r-38v, 43r-56v, 59r-76v, the letters are
                        large and broad, angular; some letters have hairlines and serifs.
                        </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic"> Hand b: <locus from="11r" to="14v">11r-14v</locus>, 27r-32v, 39r-42v, 57r-58v, the letters are slander and
                        round.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc type="findingAid">Readings are indicated by the names of days of the
                              week or months written in the upper margin, in a secondary hand:
                              ዘቀዳ[ም]: <locus target="#32rb">fol. 32rb</locus> [ዘት]ስብዕት: <locus target="#34va">fol. 34va</locus> ዘ&lt;…&gt;ለት: <locus target="#44rb">fol. 44rb</locus> ዘጥምቀት: <locus target="#50ra">fol.
                                 50ra</locus> ዘጥምቀት: <locus target="#58rb">fol. 58rb</locus> ምንባብ:
                              በእሑድ: <locus target="#63vb">fol. 63vb</locus> በጸሎተ፡ ሐሙስ: <locus target="#74vb">fol. 74vb</locus>.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc>- Omitted letters, words or passages are written in the margins or inserted interlineally, in the main hands: fols. 24va, 25va, 38rb, 43rb, 46rb, 49ra. - Tämälläs-sign, in the shape of two perpendicular lines, indicating the place where the omissions written in the margins, in hand a, belong: fols. 24ra l.20, 25va l.12, 52ra l.3, 52rb l.11. - Small squares are drawn in ink within the text: <locus target="#8ra">fol.  8ra</locus>. - Minor notes, writing exercises, doodles: fols. 8v, 9r, 12v, 13r, 29r, 75v, 76v.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding contemporary="false">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">Both boards are missing.
 Two pairs of sewing
                           stations.</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial"/>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b3" type="Endbands"/>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b4" type="Other">Small holes are visible in the centre
                           fold of the quires, one close to the head and one close to the tail of
                           the codex.</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b5">None</decoNote>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
               </physDesc>
               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0111SSB">Bet Ḥawāryāt / SSB</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1850" notAfter="1900">Second half of the 19th cent.
                        (?)</origDate>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>Names of the original donors have been erased
                     from the supplication formulas and replaced with the names Gabra Ḥǝywat, Walda
                     Mikāʾel, Säbänä Giyorgis, Walda Yoḥannǝs, Walda Kidān, Za-Walda Māryām and
                     Walatta Māryām, in a secondary hand.
 One of the original donors' names,
                     Mǝslä ʾAntǝya, has been preserved on <locus target="#29ra">29ra</locus> and
                     42rb.</provenance>
               </history>
               
